French_language\", \"score\": 0.9958959470350734, \"rank\": 0.003231200008935289, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1250}, {\"ngram\": \"the hijab\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1280}, {\"ngram\": \"any sportsperson\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"accordance\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC said: 'This means that they must respect the principles of secularism (la\\u00efcit\\u00e9) and neutrality, which, according to French law, means prohibition from wearing outwardly religious symbols, including the hijab, veil and headscarf when they are acting in their official capacity and on official occasions as members of the French national team.'\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.733889191480847e-27, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"score\": 0.999999663404253, \"rank\": 2.976493285580725e-07, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9917254914241888, \"rank\": 0.005538109845996922, \"text\": \"French national team\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fr